page.title: 04Isel road estate
page.content: There are three types of houses on the estate, detatched, semi-detached and bungalows. Most of the houses are semi-detached, a small percentage are detached and bungalows. The estate was built in the late 1950's and is bordered on one side by the Castlegate site of Cockermouth school and on the other by the cottage hospital. In the centre of the estate there is a large green area for recreation and there is also a small park on the north edge of the estate. There are no shops on the estate, but there several post boxes.
